Space Exploration Technologies, or SpaceX, is an American space transportation company founded in June 2002 by Elon Musk, an early investor in PayPal. It has developed partially reusable Falcon 1 and Falcon 9 launch vehicles. SpaceX also develops Dragon series spacecraft to launch through Falcon 9. SpaceX mainly designs, tests and manufactures internal components, such as Merlin, Kestrel and Draco rocket engines. In 2008, SpaceX received the NASA formal contract.
